The JavaMaildir Project

   JavaMaildir is a JavaMail service provider. It provides an access method
   to qmail-style Maildir folders extended to support courier-imap Maildir++
   standard. Maildir++ was slightly modified to overcome rather odd
   courier-imap's notion of "INBOX." as a root.

     ----------------------------------------------------------------------

   Features:
     * 100% pure Java
     * JavaMail compliant
     * Folders: create, rename, delete, list contents
     * Messages: read, append(create), delete, move, copy. Full MIME support.
     * Events: folder created, deleted, renamed; message added, removed, changed
     * Misc: gracefuly handle external deliveries and message removes

     ----------------------------------------------------------------------

   JavaMaildir uses the following libraries:
     * Apache-Ant
     * Apache-Jarkarta-Log4j
     * Apache-Jarkarta-Commons-Collections
     * Apache-Jarkarta-Commons-Lang

     ----------------------------------------------------------------------

   Related specifications:
     * JavaMail
     * Maildir
     * Maildir++

     ----------------------------------------------------------------------

   Related projects:
     * Local Store

     ----------------------------------------------------------------------

   Installation and Usage:

    Installation and usage is straightforward - put javamaildir.jar into you classpath and run examples.
